&lt;p&gt;Innovation is at the heart of what we do. At Implicit, we&#39;re building the world&#39;s leading AI Knowledge Engine for Maintenance and Support. We provide the trusted, accurate knowledge foundation for the hybrid workforce. Implicit is a secure, no-code AI platform that transforms complex, unstructured documentation and data into structured knowledge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a part-time full-stack developer to join our team in the United States. As a Full-Stack Developer at Implicit, you will work closely with our data science and product teams to build the next-generation AI product support platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join Implicit and come work with some of the world’s most talented data scientists, engineers, and thought leaders.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;As a Full-Stack Developer, you will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Agentic Development:&amp;nbsp; &lt;/strong&gt;Work with maximum productivity using modern agentic coding tools such as Claude Code, Cursor, and Playwright Agents.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Develop and Maintain Web Interfaces&lt;/strong&gt;: Build responsive and interactive web applications using modern front-end technologies like React, Redux, React Query, styled modules, SASS, Tailwind, Ant Components.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Backend Services: &amp;nbsp; &lt;/strong&gt;Help to develop various backend services in Java, Spring Boot, Python, FastAPI, Postgres, Docker.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Testing and QA:&amp;nbsp; &lt;/strong&gt;Maintain high quality code by focusing on Test-Driven Development, using Playwright, Vitest, React Testing Library, test agents.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaborate with Teams&lt;/strong&gt;: Work closely with the product team to implement designs and ensure that they are fully optimized across all platforms and browsers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Write Clean, Maintainable Code&lt;/strong&gt;: Ensure that code is modular, well-structured, and follows best practices for performance, scalability, and maintainability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Optimize Web Performance&lt;/strong&gt;: Focus on improving the performance of web applications through techniques like lazy loading, code splitting, and optimizing assets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Debug and Troubleshoot&lt;/strong&gt;: Identify issues, debug problems, and optimize the front-end code for improved speed and reliability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contribute to Code Reviews&lt;/strong&gt;: Participate in code reviews to maintain high coding standards and learn from team members.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stay Up-to-Date with AI Development Trends&lt;/strong&gt;: Continuously learn and implement new front-end technologies, techniques, and best practices to improve development efficiency and the quality of the end product.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A minimum of 5+ years of full stack development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in React, Typescript, and backend development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with REST APIs and asynchronous programming.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of test frameworks such as Playwright and Vitest.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of version control systems (Git) and collaborative development workflows (GitHub, GitLab, etc.).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to translate designs into high-quality, pixel-perfect user interfaces with a strong understanding of user experience best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent team player with strong written and verbal English communication skills. Ability to work effectively in a collaborative environment, especially with remote or cross-functional teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;This position requires US Citizens residing currently in the US due to government work&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Marketing Analyst / Intern (Part-Time)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Implicit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Innovation is at the heart of what we do. At Implicit, we have built the world&#39;s first No-Code Knowledge Engine for building AI Experts. Our platform enables teams to turn multiple content sources into powerful, production-ready AI systems without writing code.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Check out the app here (free account): &lt;a href=&quot;https://app.implicitcloud.com/register&quot;&gt;app.implicitcloud.com/register&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re seeking a part-time Marketing Analyst or Intern to help build our marketing presence and create compelling content that communicates our value to customers. This is a hands-on role suited for someone who wants to learn B2B SaaS marketing while contributing meaningfully to a growing company.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build public AI experts that showcase Implicit&#39;s value&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plan and execute social media campaigns across LinkedIn, Reddit, X, and other relevant platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track campaign performance and report on key metrics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research competitors and industry trends to inform messaging&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support content creation for the website, blog, and email campaigns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with event marketing and webinar promotion as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Nurture and support community of AI Expert builders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Currently pursuing or recently completed a degree in Marketing, Communications, Business, or related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong writing skills with ability to translate technical concepts into clear, compelling content&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong research skills to build public AI experts on diverse topics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with social media platforms, particularly LinkedIn&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-starter comfortable working independently&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interest in B2B technology and enterprise software&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with design tools (Canva, Figma) or marketing platforms (HubSpot, Hootsuite) a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Details&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Type: Part-time (approximately 20 hours per week)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Duration: 8 weeks (possibility of extension)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Location: Remote&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Compensation: $20 to $25 per hour (based on experience)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience Level: Student, recent graduate, or early-career professional&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
